- `cli.RequireStdin()` can be used to wait for stdin (blocking, buffered, from a bash pipe etc..)
- `cli.WithMingledOpts()` can be used to allow mingled short ops (getopt like)
- `cli.WithHelp()` can be used to generate a help flag
- `cli.WithVersion(int)` can be used to generate a version flag. I like release timestamps for clis so thats the default
- `cli.WithMan()` creates a manpage from the readme of the repo using pandoc
- `cli.WithCompletetion()` creates a simple script for `complete X`


